  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Administrator MySideline Sync provides comprehensive management and monitoring of external system integration with MySideline. This includes configuring synchronization settings, monitoring data transfers, managing API connections, handling synchronization errors, and ensuring data consistency between systems. MySideline integration is essential for maintaining accurate carnival data and ensuring seamless data flow between platforms.</p>

  <h3>Access Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Administrator Role</strong> — Must be logged in with admin privileges</li>
    <li><strong>Integration Management</strong> — Authority to configure and manage external integrations</li>
    <li><strong>API Configuration</strong> — Access to API settings and authentication credentials</li>
    <li><strong>Data Synchronization</strong> — Ability to initiate and monitor data synchronization</li>
    <li><strong>Direct Access</strong> — Available via `/admin/mysideline-sync`</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>MySideline Integration Capabilities</h3>

  <h4>Data Synchronization</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Carnival Data Sync</strong> — Synchronize carnival information from MySideline</li>
    <li><strong>Club Data Sync</strong> — Import and update club information from external systems</li>
    <li><strong>Player Data Sync</strong> — Synchronize player registration and participation data</li>
    <li><strong>Results Data Sync</strong> — Import carnival results and competition outcomes</li>
    <li><strong>Real-time Updates</strong> — Receive real-time updates from MySideline</li>
